    Autocreate
    Properties that are null and are annotated with @Autocreate will be populated automatically during an assignment of a subproperty. If a block is supplied, the block will be called to create the new object, otherwise the parameterless contructor will be used. Copyright 2010 Guidewire Software, Inc.

    RpcWebService
    The @RpcWebService annotation is used to expose a class as an RPC/Encoded web service. The preferred way to expose a web service, however, is to use the @WsiWebService annotation instead.
    RpcWebServiceMethod
    The WebServiceMethod annotation is used to set properties of a single web service operation within a WebService class. Restrictions. A. The method must be public B. The method must be a part of a Gosu class with the 'WebService' annotation. Any conflicts between settings defined in the class level 'WebService' annotation and this method level annotation will resolve to the method level annotation. This annotation is not required to exposed web service methods, all public methods of a class with the 'WebService' annotation are exposed by default (unless the 'DoNotPublish' annotation is set).
